    "XII], [Boa15a, §2] and [DHMS20]) and the case of quadratic monomial exponents at infinity (also called the case of pure Gaussian type, see e.g.",
    "[Sab16], [Ho22]).",
    "Beyond these cases, it has proved difficult to determine the Fourier transform of Stokes data outside of some specific situations (see e.g.",
